com.intel.icecp.node.utils

Class CircularBufferCache<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.intel.icecp.node.utils.CircularBufferCache<T>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Cache<T>

    public class CircularBufferCache<T>
extends Object
implements Cache<T>
    Maintains a limited cache of objects, replacing the older elements first. It relies on one user-level condition when adding new items: the ID passed to add(long, Object) must be greater than the latest ID held in the cache. This is necessary to guarantee fast look up times (i.e. O(lg n)) when retrieving objects from the cache.

    This class is thread-safe at a very coarse level: any methods that may retrieve or modify the state of the cache are synchronized and cannot be interleaved.
